Table omt.CustomOrderTabDTO

Custom order detail tabs that should be displayed additionally.

Columns 

References[1] Column Type Constraints[2] Default Comment
id integer PK, UNIQUE, NOT_NULL nextval('"CustomOrderTabDTO_id_seq"')  
title varchar NOT_NULL The title of the tab. Also a message key can be used. 
url varchar NOT_NULL The url the content of the tab should be loaded from. 
row integer NOT_NULL 1 The row at the order details page in which the tab should be displayed for.
Default is the first row. 
rank integer The ascending order the tab should be displayed in. 
active boolean NOT_NULL true Whether the tab should be displayed. 
RightDefDO rightDefRef integer The permission that is required for this tab. If not set, no permission is required. 
secure boolean NOT_NULL false Whether to enable requesting the url with security methods. 

[1] Not all references are enforced by a foreign key where they could.
Such "missing" foreign keys are denoted with [[ ]].

[2] Constraints:
PK : the column is part of the primary key
UNIQUE: does don't cover unique constraints and indexes defined on more than one column.

Constraints and Indexes 

Type Name Definition
PRIMARY KEY CustomOrderTabDTO_pk PRIMARY KEY (id) 
FOREIGN KEY CustomOrderTabDTO_fk_RightDefDO FOREIGN KEY ("rightDefRef") REFERENCES "RightDefDO"(id)
